					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-1587502#post-2450758</guid>
				<title>Re: @TL333s</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-1587502/on-the-efficiency-of-various-postal-services#post-2450758</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Wed, 03 Feb 2016 13:28:17 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Eta Carinae</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>2110706</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Mmh.<br /> As soon as I read SCP-2699 (with Holiday Gift in mind), I thought about continuing on letters and involving 343. How could I not? I must say that if I'd known in advance I would submit this to the site, I'd probably have thought twice about it.<br /> Then, as I was developing the tale to post it, I just liked the contrast between one god who acts as a CEO (and a wrathful one&#8230;), and another god who plays with a raptor and compares whisky brands.<br /> Can the above be considered as extenuating circumstances? ;&gt;</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
